Author: WEKEY
Vol / Page: 61
Edition:
Quote: (quoting Otago Gfds Regs) Claims shall be classified thus;- 1. Ordinary Claims, <i>i.e.</i>, alluvial claims worked without the aid of sluices or machines. 2. Sluice and machine claims, <i>i.e.</i>, alluvial claims worked with the aid of sluices or puddling machines. 3. Wet Claims, <i>i.e.</i>., alluvial claims in flooded ground ... 4. Creek or river claims, <i>i.e.</i>, alluvial claims in the bed of creeks or rivers. 5. Quartz claims.
